data.enText: an act of trying to do sth, especially sth difficult, often with no success

data.chText: 为削减费用，关闭了两家工厂。
data.enText: Two factories were closed in an attempt to cut costs.
They made no attempt to escape.

data.chText: 我考汽车驾驶执照一次就通过了。
data.enText: I passed my driving test at the first attempt .

data.chText: 这对夫妇试图和解但未成功。
data.enText: The couple made an unsuccessful attempt at a compromise.
an act of trying to kill sb
Someone has made an attempt on the President's life .
an effort to do better than sth, such as a very good performance in sport

data.chText: 他为创造陆上速度世界纪录所作的尝试
data.enText: his attempt on the world land speed record
to make an effort or try to do sth, especially sth difficult

data.chText: 我将努力回答你的全部问题。
data.enText: I will attempt to answer all your questions.

data.chText: 不要试图自己修理这个东西。
data.enText: Do not attempt to repair this yourself.

data.chText: 囚犯企图逃跑，但失败了。
data.enText: The prisoners attempted an escape, but failed.

simple_means.memory_skill: at 加强 + tempt 尝试 → 尝试，企图

ex.zh: 尝试控制/寻找/阻止/解决

example: attacks on women increased last year
they made an attempt on his life

tr: earnest and conscientious activity intended to do or accomplish something
example: made an effort to cover all the reading material
wished him luck in his endeavor
she gave it a good try

tr: enter upon an activity or enterprise

example: He tried to shake off his fears
The infant had essayed a few wobbly steps
The police attempted to stop the thief
She always seeks to do good in the world

value.def: If you attempt to do something, especially something difficult, you try to do it.

example.ex: The only time that we attempted to do something like that was in the city of Philadelphia...
example.tran: 只有在费城那次我们曾试着做那样的事。

example.ex: Before I could attempt a reply he added over his shoulder: 'Wait there.'
example.tran: 还没等我回答他就回头又说了一句：“在那儿等着。”

value.tran: 尝试，试图（尤指做困难的事）

value.def: If you make an attempt to do something, you try to do it, often without success.

example.ex: ...a deliberate attempt to destabilise the defence...
example.tran: 经过深思熟虑的破坏该防御的尝试

example.ex: It was one of his rare attempts at humour.
example.tran: 那是他极不常见的想要表现幽默的一次。

example.ex: ...their involvement in a coup attempt in September.
example.tran: 他们参与了9月的那场失败的政变

gramarinfo.label: usu with supp, oft N to-inf

value.tran: （通常指不成功的）尝试，企图，试图

value.def: An attempt on some-one's life is an attempt to kill them.

example.ex: ...an attempt on the life of the former Iranian Prime Minister.

value.def: In British English, if a sportsman or sportswoman makes an attempt on a sporting record, they try to beat it. In American English you say that they make an attempt to break it.

example.ex: Everything is almost ready for me to make another attempt on the record.
example.tran: 一切几乎都已准备就绪，就等我向纪录发起再一次冲击了。

value.tran: （运动员创造纪录的）尝试，冲击

trans: 尝试；企图做；试图；试图做
努力；试图做某些事情；试着做某事

partsOfSpeech.dec: at 加强 + tempt 尝试 → 尝试，企图
tempt 尝试 + ation 行为，过程，状态，结果 → 想尝试一下 → 诱惑
tempt 尝试 + atious 有…性质的 → 诱惑性的
tempt 尝试 + ing 令人…的 → 吸引人的；动人的
con 加强 + tempt 蔑视 → 轻视
contempt 轻视 + ible 可…的 → 可轻视的；下贱的
contempt 轻视 + uous …的 → 瞧不起人的
